de.malkusch.whoisServerList.compiler

Class DomainListCompiler

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.malkusch.whoisServerList.compiler.DomainListCompiler

  • @Immutable
public final class DomainListCompiler
extends Object
    Compiles a list of top level domains and its whois server. The sources for the compiled list are:
    • Whois Server List
    • Root Zone Database
    • Public Suffix List
    Author:
    markus@malkusch.de
    See Also:
    Whois Server List, Root Zone Database, Public Suffix List, Donations

      • compile

        public de.malkusch.whoisServerList.api.v1.model.DomainList compile()
                                                            throws BuildListException,
                                                                   InterruptedException
        Compiles and returns the merged list from all list sources. The date of the compiled list is set to now. The patch part of the version is incremented by 1. E.g. version 1.0.0 will be 1.0.1.
        Returns:
        the compiled list
        Throws:
        BuildListException - If building a list failed
        InterruptedException - If the thread was interrupted
